Usage: chpl [flags] [source files]

Compilation Traces:
      --print-commands  Print system commands
      --print-passes    Print compiler passes

Code Size Statistics:
      --count-tokens    Count tokens
      --print-code-size Print code size statistics

Optimization Control:
      --no-bounds-checks
                        Disable bounds checking
      --no-copy-propagation
                        Disable copy propagation
      --no-expand-iterators-inline-opt
                        Disable the expansion of iterators inlined around loop bodies
      --no-inline       Do not inline functions
      --no-single-loop-iterator-opt
                        Disable the optimization of iterators composed of a single loop
      --unoptimized     Generate naive code (many temps)

Code Generation:
      --[no-]cg-cpp-lines
                        Generate #line annotations
  -g, --[no-]debug      Allow debugging of generated C code
  -O, --[no-]optimize   Optimize generated C code
  -p, --parallel        Toggle threaded code generation
      --savec <path>    Save generated C code in directory

Linker Control:
      --ccflags <flags> Back-end C compiler flags
  -l, --lib-linkage <path>
                        C library linkage
  -L, --lib-search-path <path>
                        C library search path
  -o, --output <name>   Name output executable

Miscellaneous Flags:
      --chplhome <path> Over-ride $CHPL_HOME
      --[no-]devel      Compile as developer
      --explain-call <call>[:<module>][:<line>]
                        Explain resolution of call
      --instantiate-max <max>
                        Limit number of instantiations
      --no-warnings     Disable output of warnings
  -s, --set <name>[=<value>]
                        Set config param value

Compiler Information:
      --copyright       Show Copyright
  -h, --help            Help (show this list)
      --license         Show License
      --version         Show Version
